<PropertyList>

 <title>LZ-129 Hindenburg</title>
 <key>
  <name>?</name>
  <desc>Display this message.</desc>
 </key>

 <!-- Specific keys -->
 <key>
  <name>s</name>
  <desc>Drop fore ballast in 0.1% decrements.</desc>
 </key>
 <key>
  <name>S</name>
  <desc>Drop foreballast in 1% decrements.</desc>
 </key>
 <key>
  <name>d</name>
  <desc>Drop aft ballast in 0.1% decrements.</desc>
 </key>
 <key>
  <name>D</name>
  <desc>Drop aft ballast in 1% decrements.</desc>
 </key>
 <key>
  <name>W</name>
  <desc>Weigh-off to 10% of current weight by dropping ballast. (Takes about 10 seconds and only works on ground.)</desc>
 </key>
 <!-- Handling instructions. -->
 <line>Take-off</line>
 <line></line>
 <line>1. Weigh-off (W) twice.</line>
 <line>2. Drop ballast fore and aft if needed.</line>
 <line>3. Start engines once the airship is clear of the ground.</line>
 <line>4. Stay in control by careful use of elevator and rudder. (I only manage to do so for a few minutes..)</line>
 <line>5. ...</line>
 <line>6. Don't Panic!</line>

</PropertyList>